            <odd id="aspace_98ff8674e9f3605eda0a9b24aa4dd0b2">
               <head>General</head>
               <p>Engraved or published by G. Barrett</p>
               <p>Copper plate maker's mark on verso: B. Whittow &amp; Son. No. 31 Shoe Lane, Holborn London</p>
            </odd>
            <scopecontent id="aspace_759b5599cc0e8112f991d0f3271cba0f">
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
               <p>Accompanied by plate wrapper with imprint: Herst, Richard. Engraved by G. Barrett. A Catholic suspected of harbouring priests. A warrant was issued to apprehend him as a recusant, and in a scuffle that took place on of the officers was killed. Herst escaped, but came forward to take his trial, and was found guilty as accessory to the murder, and executed 26th August, 1628.</p>
            </scopecontent>
         </c>
